Command.script: this.stop()
this.hideClaim();

this.pause()
this.changeText('Here is another node. And we have connected them via WebSockets.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('The concept of node is a bit abstract. Let\'s turn them into server and client.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Now imagine we have this object on the server. Client can subscribe.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('When client subscribe, this will receive a copy of the object.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('What happen if server mutate the object?')

this.pause()
this.changeText('When the server mutates the object this sends the mutation to all the subscribers. So now we have client and server up to date.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Now is the client who wants to mutate the object.')
this.pause() this.changeText('When client mutates the object, server will not receive the mutation. But why?')

this.pause() this.changeText('Mutations are unidirectional. Remember this, because is the principle of this protocol. Only the owner of the object will emit mutations to subscribers. Server is the owner in this case.')
this.pause() this.changeText('Dop allows us to call remote functions (RPC). So what we can do, is define a function on the server. And this function will be available on the client.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('But before we use the rename function. Let\'s complicate our architecture a little bit. Remember we were working with nodes? We can connect as many nodes as we want.')

this.pause() this.changeText('We just connected one node to our original server. And another browser connected via WebRTC to our original client. But we are still out of sync. Let\'s see what happen if our last node call the function rename("Josema")')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Browser 2 call the function of browser 1. But this knows that the real owner of the function is the main server.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Server has received the call, will mutate the object and send it to the subscribers.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Both subscribers receive the mutation, but only the first one will reflect the change. Browser 1 won\'t send anything to Browser 2 because the name is the same.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Yeah!! We have all the nodes up to date!')

this.pause()
this.changeText('todo')
